result.name: sen-ryo

reviews.text: The newly renovated shop is decorated with traditional Japanese paper (Washi) which brings a distinctive and purest dining experience to the crowd.  Don't forget to try out their new summer menu this July.
Quality sushi chain restaurant, not the high-end type but sushi and seafood are fresh and tasty.  Seasonal menu available.  Usually a bit crowded during dinner time, expect to queue for some time.

Good environment but service is not good enough. Ordered the limited sashimi platter but no one introduced what’s on the plate... One of the waitress seemed to know nothing she just kept nodding her head. Also, this senryo is quite small, so reserving a table beforehand is recommended.

I can’t express enough how bad this place is , rude customer service , expensive platter and sushi taste so bad , rice not good , , waste of 360 hkd for them money has no meaning , just come pay and go worse than McDonald’s , I honesty had better experience at McDonald’s than this sushi
Quality sushi. Very fresh and the sushi rice is seasoned beautifully. The staff there were very attentive. But expect it to be quite pricey.
